SIMPLE: shocking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shocking
<hw>Shock"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Causing to shake or tremble, as
by a blow; especially, causing to recoil with horror or disgust;
extremely offensive or disgusting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The grossest and most <qex>shocking</qex> villainies.</q>
<rj><qau>Secker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Shock"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Shock"ing*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- Shock troops, a highly trained or seasoned group within an army
used to spearhead a strong offensive action. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shod</ent>⟦br⟧
